# Vercel Web Analytics Implementation

Successfully implemented Vercel Web Analytics for the Next.js App Router project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics@^1.6.1` using npm
- Updated `package.json` to include the new dependency
- Updated `package-lock.json` with the new dependency tree

### 2. Analytics Integration
Modified `app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next"`
- Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<body>` tag, placed after the WalletContextProvider and children
- The Analytics component is positioned at the end of the body to ensure proper tracking without interfering with existing functionality

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows Vercel's recommended pattern for App Router projects:
- Analytics component is imported from `@vercel/analytics/next`
- Component is placed in the root layout file to track all pages
- Positioned within the body tag after all other content to ensure optimal performance

## Build & Testing

✅ Build completed successfully with `npm run build`
✅ Linter executed - no new errors introduced in modified files
✅ TypeScript compilation passed
✅ All existing functionality preserved

## Files Modified

1. `app/layout.tsx` - Added Analytics import and component
2. `package.json` - Added @vercel/analytics dependency
3. `package-lock.json` - Updated dependency lockfile

## Notes

- The Analytics component will automatically track page views and Web Vitals
- Analytics data will be available in the Vercel dashboard once deployed
- No additional configuration is required - the component works out of the box
- The implementation preserves all existing providers, components, and styling
